Cell["\<\
To set up SpinDynamica you need to append the location of your SpinDynamica \
directory to the existing value of $Path. This is done with the following \
syntax: \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.54436460740441*^9, 
  3.544364672153332*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"eb079688-a94b-46a7-ac0c-\
2ee6169b1b95"],

Cell[TextData[StyleBox["$Path = Append[$Path, \"..insert here the name of \
your spin dynamica directory\"]",
 FontWeight->"Bold"]], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.544364676445099*^9, 3.544364706532217*^9}, 
   3.544791724850593*^9},ExpressionUUID->"4c68b992-e267-458c-9bd6-\
327d299251f1"],

Cell["\<\
The best way to do this is to type in $Path=Append[$Path
and then use the front end menu Insert>FilePath.. to locate and paste in the \
directory you need in the current syntax. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.544364709639974*^9, 
  3.544364918125247*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d373d21a-eaf1-4043-a60f-\
70d48bf8c286"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Unfortunately, you immediately encounter an annoying limitation of the ",
 StyleBox["Mathematica",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " front end (version 11). For the most part ",
 StyleBox["Mathematica",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " is well implemented, but it does have some blots, and this is one of them. \
To use the FilePath command, you need to locate a file within the directory, \
not the directory itself. To get round this you need to open the directory \
you want, locate a single file, paste this in, and then delete the last part \
of the file name until you get back to the top SpinDynamica directory itself. \
Then you type the closing bracket ] and execute the command (Shift-Return on \
a Mac). "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.544364709639974*^9, 3.544365033894236*^9}, {
   3.544365128147943*^9, 3.5443651746449957`*^9}, {3.544380522343605*^9, 
   3.54438054972377*^9}, 3.605807992811129*^9, {3.916897312739565*^9, 
   3.916897315224071*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"363dfc35-9312-4b75-b394-\
230d99b83a03"],

Cell["\<\
This is fairly annoying and hopefully Wolfram will correct this limitation in \
future releases. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.54438055776905*^9, 
  3.5443805769758472`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"2961fa1c-e83d-4d1b-8c43-\
6b2f1e9d926f"],

