Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["global using Autoload", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.544364339916782*^9, 3.5443643427703886`*^9}, {
  3.544364427584949*^9, 3.544364429943942*^9}, {3.544368692849364*^9, 
  3.54436870182403*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"5a6832e8-e56d-4b54-9387-\
4d06da9ea5ff"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "In order to set the $Path automatically, every time you start the ",
 StyleBox["Mathematica",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " kernel, you can place the instructions above in a file called ",
 StyleBox["init.m",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " in the Autoload directory of ",
 StyleBox["Mathematica",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " (for example, in ~/Library/",
 StyleBox["Mathematica",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "/Autoload/FrontEnd). To create this file, you generate a notebook ",
 StyleBox["init.nb",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " in the same directory, type in the $Path instructions as above, select all \
the cells in the notebook (Edit>Select All) set all the cells to \
Initialization cells (Cell>Cell Properties> Initialization Cell) and then \
save the notebook. You should get a prompt asking you if you want to create \
an executable file, to which you say yes. The file ",
 StyleBox["init.m",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " should then be created automatically.  To edit this file, you always edit ",
 StyleBox["init.nb",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", not the executable file ",
 StyleBox["init.m",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ". The executable will be updated whenever init.nb is saved."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.544364349834369*^9, 3.544364350250147*^9}, {
  3.5443683741614447`*^9, 3.544368592267414*^9}, {3.544368634395348*^9, 
  3.544368716248068*^9}, {3.544380624626451*^9, 3.544380634134532*^9}, {
  3.545061216995442*^9, 
  3.545061227136446*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"5c9deb36-69ce-4868-ad60-\
e13ca142e1af"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "You can check that these instructions load correctly by restarting the ",
 StyleBox["Mathematica",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " session (for example by Evaluation>Quit Kernel>Local) and then executing \
something (for example 1+1) in a new notebook. You can then evaluate $Path to \
check that your SpinDynamica directory has been appended to $Path. "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.54436877373246*^9, 3.544368867877282*^9}, {
  3.5443806378269167`*^9, 
  3.5443806567255793`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"27f57e8f-aea5-47cb-b3c0-\
6c10443f5579"]
}, Closed]]
}, Closed]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[{
 "load ",
 StyleBox["SpinDynamica",
  FontSlant->"Italic"]
}], "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.5443641699881887`*^9, 3.544364190290912*^9}, {
  3.544369304139339*^9, 3.544369312640499*^9}, {3.5443806707582207`*^9, 
  3.544380672909638*^9}, {3.7892845781505966`*^9, 
  3.789284578561015*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"ec93ce40-f6d0-4bec-8ba0-\
c65d9aa88563"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Setting $Path tells ",
 StyleBox["Mathematica",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " where the ",
 StyleBox["SpinDynamica",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " packages are but does not actually execute anything.  "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.544369317969567*^9, 3.544369351383058*^9}, {
  3.564598582639801*^9, 
  3.56459858414598*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"1b6821fd-2440-4620-b940-\
84303e593df1"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "To load ",
 StyleBox["SpinDynamica",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " you execute the following line:"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.564598490655527*^9, 
  3.564598506933628*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a074743a-36f4-4724-8ed0-\
8898348f6cce"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Needs", "[", "\"\<SpinDynamica`\>\"", "]"}]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.54436945741221*^9, 3.5443694645332*^9}, {
  3.564598513314237*^9, 3.564598515216762*^9}},
 CellLabel->
  "In[124]:=",ExpressionUUID->"f225b83f-06b5-4f6b-bea1-b0f3f9efde1a"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "You may ignore the information messages. Note that the indicated built-in \
symbols in ",
 StyleBox["Mathematica",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " are slightly modified by ",
 StyleBox["SpinDynamica, ",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "usually by adding additional functionality. In principle this could cause \
problems when executing other ",
 StyleBox["Mathematica",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " code. In particular you may find that the execution of Dot and Times is \
considerably slowed down after loading ",
 StyleBox["SpinDynamica",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ". "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7892846487599187`*^9, 3.789284779049682*^9}, {
  3.949038679354163*^9, 
  3.94903872503603*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"44aee78c-a89e-4f02-9790-\
9e7b6eb1fa48"],

Cell[TextData[{
 " So the first line of your notebook should be the ",
 ButtonBox["$Path instruction",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->"setting $Path"],
 " (see above - unless you are using Autoload) and the second line should be \
the instruction above. "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.544369354625772*^9, 3.54436945484971*^9}, {
  3.5443695542363997`*^9, 3.544369554237335*^9}, {3.544380685642705*^9, 
  3.544380693936904*^9}, {3.564598541511046*^9, 3.5645985471003847`*^9}},
 CellTags->
  "setting $Path",ExpressionUUID->"558a3fc7-bc5a-4b27-9034-beaee481194f"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]back-apostrophe\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] \
character \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]`\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] is used in ",
 StyleBox["Mathematica",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " to denote a context. "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.544369570158024*^9, 3.544369598179443*^9}, {
  3.949038738763736*^9, 
  3.9490387510649843`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"41489034-548b-457a-a891-\
af9961c8ffed"],

Cell["You can ignore the information messages for the time being. ", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.544369716552956*^9, 
  3.54436972427347*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d5332c90-a1d5-4f70-aca4-\
cd70bec945b0"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The ",
 StyleBox["Needs",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " instruction is used in ",
 StyleBox["Mathematica",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " to load a package - unless it has already been loaded, in which case it \
does nothing. "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.5443696783627*^9, 
  3.544369704042337*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"41653437-55c8-4395-9c3b-\
b1ef3431cb8a"]
}, Closed]]
}, Closed]],

