Cell["\<\
this sets up a two-spin system, with spin \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]I\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] having quantum number 1/2 and spin \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]S\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] having quantum number 3/2. \
You can load any number of spins, with any labels (including numbers) and any \
valid quantum numbers (half-odd-integers or integers)\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.544369821551723*^9, 3.5443699105094843`*^9}, 
   3.54437768715008*^9, {3.544377762871191*^9, 
   3.544377774362995*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"85c341a2-c4d5-4c1e-b935-\
9afe88ea3985"],

Cell["\<\
As another example, to set up a system of one spin, called spin #1, with \
quantum number I=3/2, one would use this instruction:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.616744151902508*^9, 
  3.616744192308848*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"6c80655c-efa6-4fc9-bf47-\
c931f9142f40"],

