   3.54479178207523*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"876464dd-7b25-4505-bf0a-\
f38ae237618d"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["SpinDynamica",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " contains numerous other routines for defining and manipulating spin \
operators, which are described in part 3 of this documentation."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.544791784817779*^9, 3.544791828244188*^9}, {
   3.57425934297439*^9, 3.5742593590766683`*^9}, 3.574847914482397*^9, {
   3.9490389645372057`*^9, 
   3.949038965429284*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"fcb30491-63e2-4827-ac48-\
9a0a50ad6047"]
}, Closed]]
}, Closed]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[" generators", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.54435961135287*^9, 3.544359628871992*^9}, {
   3.544359721544903*^9, 3.544359747254434*^9}, 3.54435989242558*^9, {
   3.544359948339938*^9, 3.544359951240794*^9}, {3.709547029391911*^9, 
   3.7095470308794484`*^9}, 
   3.745466727981201*^9},ExpressionUUID->"6981db2d-e45b-41f3-9c9a-\
9db82b629796"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "In ",
 StyleBox["SpinDynamica",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  generator means the \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]driving force\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] for the evolution of the spin system. This may be a \
hermitian spin operator defining the spin Hamiltonian, a relaxation \
superoperator, or a combination of the above. Each of these  generators may \
also be time-dependent. ",
 StyleBox["SpinDynamica",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " handles any combination of Hamiltonians and relaxation superoperators, and \
any time dependence. "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.544371341507496*^9, 3.544371361225561*^9}, {
   3.544371394124308*^9, 3.544371514622819*^9}, {3.544375601373263*^9, 
   3.544375608954443*^9}, 3.544377343343633*^9, {3.7095470397482166`*^9, 
   3.709547040840631*^9}, {3.7095470774282494`*^9, 3.709547078495871*^9}, {
   3.7454667303618717`*^9, 
   3.745466736144898*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"7bca1df1-f47b-430d-ba43-\
a937d8bbbd5d"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "In many software packages, time-dependent  generators are handled by \
slicing up the calculation into small time steps. ",
 StyleBox["SpinDynamica",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " does not work like that. ",
 StyleBox["SpinDynamica",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " uses the numerical differential equation solving capability of ",
 StyleBox["Mathematica",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", which works in a smooth and adaptive way, without time-slicing. "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.544371525348061*^9, 3.544371622208143*^9}, {
   3.5443728476291037`*^9, 3.5443728887163277`*^9}, {3.544377350317874*^9, 
   3.544377351434787*^9}, {3.709547086907291*^9, 3.7095470882313833`*^9}, 
   3.745466740484481*^9},ExpressionUUID->"471d32af-232a-4605-8d2f-\
aca5b855eb22"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["time-independent spin hamiltonians", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.54435961135287*^9, 3.544359628871992*^9}, {
   3.544359721544903*^9, 3.544359747254434*^9}, 3.54435989242558*^9, 
   3.544359960915506*^9, {3.544371332973879*^9, 3.544371335705212*^9}, {
   3.544375895939458*^9, 
   3.544375916847677*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"1ed583f6-232e-4a35-aeee-\
9a931bf0f7c5"],

Cell["\<\
Time-independent spin hamiltonians are defined just by adding together \
operators with appropriate numerical or symbolic factors. For example, a \
typical rotating-frame Hamiltonian for a 2-spin-1/2 system in solution might \
be written as follows:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.544372897573571*^9, 3.544372957538347*^9}, {
  3.5443759047811813`*^9, 3.544375918982691*^9}, {3.621572559587803*^9, 
  3.621572561661663*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"b000df7f-500f-4297-b0f7-\
e630329318e0"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Hamiltonian", "=", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"2", "\[Pi]", " ", "100", " ", 
    RowBox[{"opI", "[", 
     RowBox[{"1", ",", "\"\<z\>\""}], "]"}]}], "+", 
   RowBox[{"2", "\[Pi]", " ", 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"-", "50"}], ")"}], " ", 
    RowBox[{"opI", "[", 
     RowBox[{"2", ",", "\"\<z\>\""}], "]"}]}], "+", 
   RowBox[{"2", "\[Pi]", " ", "20", " ", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"opI", "[", "1", "]"}], ".", 
     RowBox[{"opI", "[", "2", "]"}]}]}]}]}]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.544372961197689*^9, 3.544372990322453*^9}},
 CellLabel->"In[42]:=",ExpressionUUID->"e81dbbb1-5686-4332-b40d-4e4e1d09bf97"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"40", " ", "\[Pi]", " ", 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    TagBox[
     RowBox[{
      TagBox[
       SubscriptBox[
        OverscriptBox["\<\"I\"\>", "\[RightVector]"], "1"],
       DisplayForm], 
      AdjustmentBox["\[Bullet]",
       BoxMargins->{{-0.3, 0}, {0, 0}}], 
      TagBox[
       SubscriptBox[
        OverscriptBox["\<\"I\"\>", "\[RightVector]"], "2"],
       DisplayForm]}],
     DisplayForm], ")"}]}], "+", 
  RowBox[{"200", " ", "\[Pi]", " ", 
   TagBox[
    SubscriptBox["I", 
     RowBox[{"1", "z"}]],
    DisplayForm]}], "-", 
  RowBox[{"100", " ", "\[Pi]", " ", 
   TagBox[
    SubscriptBox["I", 
     RowBox[{"2", "z"}]],
    DisplayForm]}]}]], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.544372991130419*^9, 3.544547442543303*^9, 3.5445945840333652`*^9, 
   3.544604444276827*^9, 3.544791702247837*^9, 3.544791743381871*^9, 
   3.54505766721756*^9, 3.5630538049829288`*^9, 3.564574668134196*^9, 
   3.564575454081357*^9, 3.5648114380350513`*^9, 3.572631430690664*^9, 
