   3.816851029114114*^9, 3.837780245548601*^9, 3.9101517695743937`*^9, 
   3.916897426775053*^9, 3.916897560022047*^9, 3.949038979362938*^9},
 CellLabel->"Out[42]=",ExpressionUUID->"0280bac5-ade0-4460-b79c-90042b808dc3"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "In this example, spin #1 has a resonance offset of +100 Hz, spin #2 has a \
resonance offset of -50 Hz, and there is a 20 Hz J-coupling. Note that \
frequencies in ",
 StyleBox["SpinDynamica",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " are (almost) always specified in angular units (radians per second), so \
the frequency in Hz must be multiplied by 2\[Pi]. "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.54437300500331*^9, 3.544373034128277*^9}, {
  3.544373098413917*^9, 
  3.544373138191204*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d33b49f6-15e3-40ae-bc6d-\
234e5c12176f"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "When the equation above is first written, the symbol ",
 StyleBox["Hamiltonian",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontColor->RGBColor[0, 0, 1]],
 " appears in blue, which ",
 StyleBox["Mathematica",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " uses to indicate a symbol that has not been defined yet. When the \
instruction is executed, ",
 StyleBox["Hamiltonian",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " turns black. This means that it is now defined, and its definition is \
revealed by executing it:"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.544375630102406*^9, 
  3.5443757168310747`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3db5a70f-2866-492f-a27d-\
28e94afc0ee0"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 StyleBox["Hamiltonian",
  FontWeight->"Bold"]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.544375720588834*^9, 3.544375720590308*^9}},
 CellLabel->"In[43]:=",ExpressionUUID->"597e3db4-61c4-448c-bfbc-5d5e29fff163"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"40", " ", "\[Pi]", " ", 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    TagBox[
     RowBox[{
      TagBox[
       SubscriptBox[
        OverscriptBox["\<\"I\"\>", "\[RightVector]"], "1"],
       DisplayForm], 
      AdjustmentBox["\[Bullet]",
       BoxMargins->{{-0.3, 0}, {0, 0}}], 
      TagBox[
       SubscriptBox[
        OverscriptBox["\<\"I\"\>", "\[RightVector]"], "2"],
       DisplayForm]}],
     DisplayForm], ")"}]}], "+", 
  RowBox[{"200", " ", "\[Pi]", " ", 
   TagBox[
    SubscriptBox["I", 
     RowBox[{"1", "z"}]],
    DisplayForm]}], "-", 
  RowBox[{"100", " ", "\[Pi]", " ", 
   TagBox[
    SubscriptBox["I", 
     RowBox[{"2", "z"}]],
    DisplayForm]}]}]], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{
