Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["CoherenceOrderFiltration", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.544379401151694*^9, 3.544379435793702*^9}, 
   3.8168538487718773`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"12126a23-7f8c-4f7a-9c6f-\
32f567c40cab"],

Cell["\<\
CoherenceOrderFiltration is used to filter out the components of the spin \
density operator which belong to a set of coherence orders. This can be a \
quick way to emulate the effect of phase cycling, or field gradient \
combinations. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.544380036976902*^9, 3.544380081045005*^9}, {
  3.816853869000278*^9, 
  3.816853869615358*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"85e9f267-79bc-44e0-b9a3-\
085d816f251e"],

Cell["\<\
In general, the syntax CoherenceOrderFiltration[spins,pvals] defines \
filtration by the set of coherence orders pvals, belonging to the spins \
defined in spins. If the specification spins is omitted, all of the spins in \
the current SpinSystem are used. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.588071468677699*^9, 3.588071555039419*^9}, 
   3.8168538746008234`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"60a74dc0-2641-4af1-b7c8-\
a92d1dce1183"],

Cell["\<\
For example, the syntax CoherenceOrderFiltration[p] implements filtration \
through coherence orders -1 and +2. By default, this includes all 3 spins in \
the current system:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.544380089495572*^9, 3.54438013382041*^9}, {
   3.588071564576669*^9, 3.58807158169713*^9}, {3.722565877644977*^9, 
   3.722565897302583*^9}, 3.816853881797847*^9, {3.8168539316123*^9, 
   3.816853952977274*^9}, {3.816855092128491*^9, 
   3.816855105120891*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"46654441-6ec4-4152-b780-\
9de9942ae7f2"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"CoherenceOrderFiltration", "[", 
  RowBox[{"{", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"-", "1"}], ",", "2"}], "}"}], "]"}]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.544380130967648*^9, 3.544380139551281*^9}, {
   3.588071585226816*^9, 3.5880715891155868`*^9}, 3.816853889630598*^9, {
   3.816853955747643*^9, 3.816853966435305*^9}},
 CellLabel->"In[92]:=",ExpressionUUID->"762d69db-530d-40bc-8e8c-1f4b4e08a67d"],

