Cell["\<\
defines a Gaussian pulse with maximum amplitude in the centre of the event \
but with an additional cosine modulation which has its time origin at the \
start of the event. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.544464849863714*^9, 
  3.5444648866224947`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"691469d0-eb9f-4280-ae94-\
c0757ae7e25b"],

Cell["\<\
Any number of local time variables and local time origins may be used. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.544464587926863*^9, 3.544464731379068*^9}, {
  3.5444647729236*^9, 3.544464782403439*^9}, {3.544464903887847*^9, 
  3.544464904709805*^9}, {3.544465138716954*^9, 
  3.544465139146959*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"0bed3dac-c1e7-48b7-b50b-\
a37df3c036bc"],

Cell["\<\
It is even possible to specify an event which uses both local and global time \
variables.  For example, the syntax\
\>", "Text",
