Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["adiabatic events", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.544462570428117*^9, 3.544462590712843*^9}, {
  3.54446262642469*^9, 3.544462653647873*^9}, {3.544463611296722*^9, 
  3.544463615004216*^9}, {3.544465452540286*^9, 3.544465456008657*^9}, {
  3.728215194867552*^9, 3.728215196716776*^9}},
 Background->RGBColor[0.94, 0.88, 0.94],
 CellTags->
  "ShapeFunction",ExpressionUUID->"2590e63f-db01-48a6-a989-f4dbab9084fa"],

Cell["\<\
An adiabatic event is a special case of a general time-dependent event such \
as Function, PeriodicFunction and PeriodicGeneratorFunction events. Adiabatic \
events are usually characterized by a slowly time varying Hamiltonian.

SpinDynamica may be informed over a slowly time varying event by specifying a \
PropagationMethod. Using the PropagationMethod \[Rule] Adiabatic will cause \
SpinDynamica to treat the event within the adiabatic approximation. For this \
the event is sliced up into several discrete time-intervals. To do this an \
additional user specified EventSampling has(!) to be provided. 

Frequently encountered adiabatic events in NMR involve field-cycling over a \
total duration T. Using a single integer, N, as the EventSampling scheme \
SpinDynamica will slice up the total duration T into N equal-sized intervals. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.544463723036073*^9, 3.544463816915942*^9}, {
   3.728215526430462*^9, 3.728215535313464*^9}, {3.72821556843996*^9, 
   3.7282156062735662`*^9}, {3.728215646480191*^9, 3.728216187868944*^9}, {
   3.7282164465508227`*^9, 3.728216449517742*^9}, 
   3.816848669357279*^9},ExpressionUUID->"6c36af9e-af3b-4d4b-b7f6-\
14bce2822d4d"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"adiabaticevent", "=", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"Function", "[", 
      RowBox[{"t", ",", 
       RowBox[{"2", "\[Pi]", " ", "*", 
        RowBox[{"80", "/", "5"}], "t", " ", 
        RowBox[{"opI", "[", "\"\<z\>\"", "]"}]}]}], "]"}], ",", "5", ",", 
     RowBox[{"PropagationMethod", "\[Rule]", " ", "Adiabatic"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"EventSampling", "\[Rule]", " ", 
      RowBox[{"{", "100", "}"}]}]}], "}"}]}], ";"}]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.544463819396822*^9, 3.544463898546743*^9}, {
   3.54446411212868*^9, 3.5444641152218027`*^9}, 3.564575613106921*^9, {
   3.65772865880201*^9, 3.657728664283324*^9}, {3.7282161913907175`*^9, 
   3.728216257283908*^9}, {3.7282163568072658`*^9, 3.728216392781603*^9}},
 CellLabel->
  "In[149]:=",ExpressionUUID->"5978c0e6-56ed-49ed-86db-84d09fbc7fd0"],

Cell["\<\

The field-cycling would now be performed over a time-interval of 5 seconds \
and the event would be sliced up into 100 equally spaced time-intervals.

For more details on adiabatic events and related routines consult part 11 of \
the documentation.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.54446390422744*^9, 3.54446409786101*^9}, {
  3.544464181553607*^9, 3.54446419673528*^9}, {3.544464436332293*^9, 
  3.544464467930915*^9}, {3.72821626586229*^9, 
  3.728216333793081*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d11f4f9a-c312-40da-958c-\
047b19354e55"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Closed]],

