   3.7583058678685102`*^9},
 Background->RGBColor[
  1, 0.925, 0.925],ExpressionUUID->"d42c7031-a629-4f2c-964d-e2d3e1a8c60d"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The internal routines of SpinDynamica contain many calls of the Mathematica \
Chop function, which sets numerical values less than a threshold value to \
identically zero. The default threshold for the chop threshold is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["10", 
    RowBox[{"-", "10"}]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "1dfb945b-c96a-460b-8571-f9e4466ecd2b"],
 ", which works well enough for most NMR calculations. However EPR \
calculations often employ shorter timescales and larger spin interactions. A \
default chop threshold DefaultChopThreshold has been introduced to allow user \
control. A smaller value of DefaultChopThreshold is recommended for EPR \
calculations."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.544605187857535*^9, 3.544605358555483*^9}, {
  3.5446054963115883`*^9, 3.54460550278627*^9}, {3.5446056844129553`*^9, 
  3.544605695140399*^9}, {3.544605732574442*^9, 3.544605751305723*^9}, {
  3.758305871298383*^9, 3.7583058778777885`*^9}},
 Background->RGBColor[
  1, 0.925, 0.925],ExpressionUUID->"15632b2b-d361-4297-943b-68dcfa6602f4"],

Cell["This is the default behaviour:", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.544605365411522*^9, 3.544605367124253*^9}, {
  3.544605446744529*^9, 3.544605452041113*^9}},
 Background->RGBColor[
  1, 0.925, 0.925],ExpressionUUID->"ae4e8c98-01d2-4871-81df-86ea07e7d1d2"],

